reviewText: He is a legend. Amazing piano player, Amazing melodic song writer. Lost some high range, but handled with grace and subtlety First saw him, with just 3 other players, 2 of whom are still with him 45 years later. Dee Murray, his bassist died. Davy Johnston & Nigel Olson superior guitarist & drummer. The one down side, with his elaborate show, they don't get to shine as much as they used to. Would love a live DVD of just the 4 of them. Check out 11-17-70, an early solo work from Elton.
